{
  "answer": "The elegy is **\"Saqaliya\"** (Chapter 21 of *Bang-E-Dara Part 2* by Allama Iqbal), mourning Sicily as the \"grave of Hejazi civilization.\"[^1]\n\nIt likens the speaker's lament to \"the nightingale of Shiraz\" weeping for Baghdad and to \"Ibn Badrun\" over Granada.[^2]\n\nThe closing couplet is:\n\n> I shall carry you as a gift to Hindustan;  \n> I weep here myself, to make others weep there.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/21-saqaliya/translation/#p-08760e).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraphs](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/21-saqaliya/translation/#p-02c3ef#p-83813c).\n\n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/21-saqaliya/translation/#p-665fb2).",
